metadata.name: Lost Twins #244
metadata.description:
Individually, the mints of this token are very simple. Each mint generates half of two cube forms, and each half is assigned random hues (in multiples of 10, from 0 to 360). Collectively as a project, this token challenges the approach of looking for "rarities" in a new way. How the cubes are rendered leaves the possibility for multiple mints to potentially join up on the sides with colors that perfect match each other. Will you find your lost twin?

Made in p5js
Created November 2021
Artist: @Yazid

metadata.name: Deconstructions #172
metadata.description:
Deconstructions is a further experiment with blending 3 colors and 3 different textures to create structural/abstract compositions. It's a search for beauty within asymmetrical/unsynchronized forms and disharmonic structures.


Probabilities;

- 18 compositions with variations.

- 2 background colors.

- 3 different particle starting placements.

- 21 different base color palettes. (1 monochrome) 

- 2 different alpha types; tangential & randomized.

- Different edges.

- Several starting positions and styles (wavy or straight).

Additional animation features with different shapes, angles, direction and style.


In live mode, press ‘s’ to save as .png (1500x2000 px)

It can take up to a minute to render or longer in low-performance computers. Enjoy the process!


Made with p5.js

Ilgın İçözü, May 2022
@distcollective

metadata.name: Outside your Window #79
metadata.description:
Never take for granted that we sit in the safety of our homes, behind our windows, sheltered from the elements outside. 

The characteristics of the rain outside the window, and the window itself, will be determined by the mint hash. However, the background color of this piece will constantly change based on the hour of day it is loaded, hence note that the thumbnail will only technically be accurate 1/24 hours out of the day as it represents a static snapshot taken at the time of token rendering.

100% of the primary proceeds will be donated towards flood relief efforts for the devastating December 2021 floods in Malaysia.

Made in p5js
Created December 2021
Artist: @Yazid

metadata.name: Boids 2D #119
metadata.description:
'Boids 2D' is a Generative Token that represent the flocking of birds over a landscape. The name 'Boids' comes from a famous computer animation / simulation program.

The landscape is rendered as a texture using a kind of warped noise as height map.

The boids are disposed along the flow lines obtained from the noise gradient. This gives the sensation that the Boids follow the undulations of the landscape.

Previously embedded in the 'Boids' (3D) Generative Token as an ester egg on 20% of iterations, now every iterations will be 2D as viewed from the sky.

Every owner of the 'Boids' (3D) GT will receive one 'Boids 2D' for free. The owner that minted a 'Boids' with ester egg will receive two 'Boids 2D' for free.

It is possible to save a 1600x1600 png with key 's'.

Sources of variations are:
- Noise warping control parameters generating different grade of complexity and different shape an the landscape and Boids flock (combined on a single number on the features).
- 21 color mapping for landscape and Boids.
- Two kind of border, solid or negative.

Features:
Palette: color palette name (21 different palettes)
NoiseControl: noise control parameter (0 - 15)
Border: the border can be in solid color or negative color (Solid, Negative)


Created by Andrea Belloni, fxhash: anbello, twitter: @Waterflowing0. Licensed under CC BY-NC-SA 4.0, see LICENSE.txt for more information.

metadata.name: Hash Effects #39
metadata.description:
Hash Effects is an introspective graphical performance that discovers its own abstract origins and morphs it into concrete forms.

The origins of these artworks lie within the transaction hash that results from minting a unique edition of the artwork. Each graphical trait in the artwork is controlled by this origin, so in essence the transaction hash is responsible for the entire artwork.

While most generative artworks hide their transaction hash in abstraction, Hash Effects shows it front and center. Each unique artwork celebrates its own transaction hash as a graphical element that morphs into various shapes over different animation scenes.

metadata.name: Alienpillars #133
metadata.description:
"A rare type of bug that supposedly arrived on a cargo ship is destroying crops on planet Uctumi, in the binary system of Extronium. A wide variety of very resistant subspecies has mutated and it is necessary to study and identify all of them to obtain a gen-activated pesticide that will work on all of their variations. The pest department of the Uctumi central government is working hard on it, and they say that these strange critters are probably related to similar species that inhabited the planet Earth of the Solar system a long time ago and have spread over the galaxy."

My second piece using the p5.js raymarcher I wrote. The drawing is made of circles and lines based on the 3D data. I wanted to try something hairy as it's easy to draw lines aligned to the surface normal with this method. I also used a shader for the frame and the glitchy/sketch features.

Features 

body color: green-red-purple-yellow-blue-black
body tone: dark-light
spots color: orange-green-blue-yellow-white
hair tips: yes-no
hair #1: short-medium-long
hair #2: short-medium-long
head size: small-medium-large
head shape: long-spherical-wide
glitchy mode: 10% chance
sketch mode: 9% chance

metadata.name: Shattered Moons #602
metadata.description:
🌘🌗🌖Shattered Moons🌔🌓🌒

Explore deep space moons through this pure SVG generative experiment.

Features:
- Striped Background
- Shadows
- Vapors
- Horizontal Vapors
- Meteors
- Colored Meteors
- White Moon (0.5%)

SVG being a vectorial format, this work can be displayed/printed at any size.
Press 's' on Live View to save the SVG.
Press 'p' on Live View using a Chromium based browser to export as PNG.

Also, to fully enjoy your piece, I'd suggest to use a Chromium based browser as the SVG renderer gives more details.
